<chapter id="resources">
  <title id="resources-title">Resources and Credits</title>

  <para id="resources.cvsbook">
  The book <citetitle pubwork="book">Open Source Development with
  CVS</citetitle> is available in electronic form from <ulink
  url="http://cvsbook.red-bean.com/">the book's web site</ulink>.
  </para>

  <para id="resources.cvsnt-manual" xreflabel="CVSNT Manual">
  The reference manual for <productname>CVSNT</productname> is available 
  <ulink url="http://www.cvsnt.org/manual/">here</ulink>.
  </para>

  <para>
  Development of TortoiseCVS has been made a lot easier thanks to a number of other projects:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://wxwidgets.org/">wxWidgets</ulink> is a GUI framework, which is used for all dialogs
  in TortoiseCVS.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://cvsnt.org/wiki">CVSNT</ulink> is the client that TortoiseCVS uses to communicate with the CVS server.
  Commercial support for CVSNT is offered by <ulink url="http://www.march-hare.com/">March Hare</ulink>.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://www.jrsoftware.org/isinfo.php">Inno Setup</ulink> is used to build the installer for TortoiseCVS.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://www.cygwin.com/">Cygwin</ulink> provides a number of UNIX tools that make building TortoiseCVS a
  lot easier.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://www.e-novative.info/software/ede.php">eDE</ulink> is a DocBook environment used for building
  the TortoiseCVS documentation.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
  <para>
  <ulink url="http://cppunit.sourceforge.net/">CppUnit</ulink> is a unit test framework which is used for testing some
  parts of TortoiseCVS.
  </para>
  </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

</chapter>

